}"Die Another Day" is the theme to the James Bond film of the same name recorded by Madonna.
The single, released in late 2002, peaked at number eight in the United States and #3 in the United Kingdom selling 167,863 copies, making it the most successful Bond theme since Duran Duran's "A View to a Kill." The song was later included on her 2003 album, American Life..
Die Another Day was the most successful Bond theme-song since the 1980s.
